headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 25 points, Daniel Gafford gave the Mavericks 15 rebounds in what could be his last start at center for a while and Dallas beat the Boston Celtics 127-120 on Thursday night in their NBA Finals rematch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klay Thompson scores 25 to lead Mavericks to 127-120 win over Boston as Davis delays Dallas debut

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 41 points, seven rebounds and six assists on Thursday night as the Minnesota Timberwolves rallied to beat the Houston Rockets 127-114.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 41 to lift Timberwolves over Houston 127-114

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 28 points, 12 assists and 10 rebounds for his 24th triple-double of the season, Michael Porter Jr. added 30 points and the Denver Nuggets won their fifth in a row by beating the Orlando Magic 112-90 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic has 24th triple-double of the season, Nuggets rout Magic 112-90

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 42 points, 17 rebounds and eight assists, and the Los Angeles Lakers blew most of a 26-point lead before hanging on to beat the Golden State Warriors 120-112 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron scores 42 points and overcomes Steph's 37 in the Lakers' 120-112 victory over the Warriors

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons had 30 points, including eight 3-pointers, and the Portland Trail Blazers won their sixth straight game with a 108-102 victory over the Sacramento Kings on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons has 30 and Blazers win sixth straight with 108-102 win over Kings

headlines.description: — All-Star Pascal Siakam scored 33 points and the Indiana Pacers overcame a 22-point deficit after losing Myles Turner to beat the Los Angeles Clippers 119-112 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 33 points to help Pacers overcome 22-point deficit in 119-112 win over Clippers
